net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler.context

Class AliasBindingContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler.context.AliasBindingContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BindingContext

    public class AliasBindingContext
extends Object
implements BindingContext

    A binding context constructed when compiling an alias.

    A alias binding context contains a reference to another source information record (SourceInfo), identifying a location within a compiled alias declaration.

    When an alias symbol in a label block is compiled, each generated transition has a source information record (SourceInfo) indicating the location of the elementary event label within the compiled alias declaration and with an AliasBindingContext as context, which contains another source information record (SourceInfo). That context's source information record indicates the location of the alias symbol that was replaced, which may be an occurrence on actual edge, or in the body of another alias declaration.

    Thus, the source object of a compiled transition's source information record (SourceInfo) does not necessarily indicate a location in a graph edge of the original model. To get a location within a graph, the source information's getGraphSourceInfo() method can be used.

    Author:
    Robi Malik
